  "narrative": "2.1(b)(2)(i) \n   \nRequirements and application \nThe facility has exceeded the maximum number of animals allowed on their license. The license has authorized up to 100 \nanimals, and the facility currently has 121 animals.  \n \nThe USDA license authorizes a specific number of animals to ensure that the facility and personnel possess adequate \nfacilities, employees and education to provide sufficient husbandry to the regulated animals. \n \nA licensee must obtain a new license before any change resulting in more than the authorized number of animals on hand \nat any single point in time during the period of licensure. To obtain the new license, the licensee must reapply for a license \nthat properly reflects the number of regulated animals on the property. Or they may reduce the number of regulated \nanimals to a number which is under the maximum threshold authorized under the current license. \n \nCorrect by June 5, 2026 \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with the licensee. \n \n n",
